quran[20]{c,v,t}:
  55,26,All that live on earth are doomed to die
  55,27,"But the face of your Lord will abide for ever, in all its majesty and glory"
  55,28,So which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny
  55,29,All who dwell in heaven and earth entreat Him. Each day some mighty task engages Him
  55,30,So which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny
  55,31,"Jinn and mankind, We shall surely find the time to judge you"
  55,32,So which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny
  55,33,"You race of jinn and mankind, if you have power to penetrate the confines of heaven and earth, then penetrate them. But this you shall not do except with Our own authority"
  55,34,So which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny
  55,35,"Flames of fire shall be lashed at you, and molten brass. There shall be none to help you"
  55,36,So which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny
  55,37,"When the sky splits asunder, and reddens like a rose or stained leather"
  55,38,so which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny
  55,39,on that day neither man nor jinnee will be asked about his sins
  55,40,So which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny
  55,41,The transgressors will be known by their looks; they shall be seized by their forelocks and their feet
  55,42,So which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny
  55,43,That is the Hell the transgressors deny
  55,44,They shall wander between fire and water fiercely seething
  55,45,So which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny